  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Set the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ Gas 7 and boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel the <strong>potatoes</strong> (chop any large potatoes in half)</p><p>Add the <strong>peeled</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 10-15 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once the potatoes are done, drain and leave them to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cooked potatoes</strong> to a baking tray with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season generously with <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min, turning halfway through or until crispy – these are your <strong>roast potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes have had an initial 10 min, pat the <strong>pork steaks</strong> dry with <strong>kitchen paper</strong></p><p>Rub them with a little <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season both sides with <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>seasoned pork steaks</strong> and cook for 4-5 min on each side or until they're browned and cooked through</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the steaks are cooking, reboil a kettle</p><p>Once done, transfer the <strong>cooked pork steaks</strong> to a clean chopping board, cover with a clean tea towel and leave them to rest for 2 min</p><p>Reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>green beans</strong> to a pot of plenty of <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook over a high heat for 4-5 min or until tender</p><p>Once cooked, drain the green beans</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>Henderson's Relish</strong> and <strong>half </strong>of the <strong>redcurrant jelly</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) in 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>redcurrant</strong> <strong>stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium heat, add 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir until sandy (if your pan is looking dry add a small knob of <strong>butter</strong>)</p><p>Whisk the <strong>redcurrant</strong> <strong>stock</strong> into the flour and cook for 2-3 min until the stock has thickened slightly</p><p>Add the <strong>clotted cream</strong> and cook for 1 min further</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>redcurrant</strong> <strong>gravy</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1766.-step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>rested pork steaks </strong>with the <strong>roast potatoes</strong>, <strong>cooked green beans </strong>and <strong>remaining redcurrant jelly</strong> to the side</p><p>Pour over the <strong>redcurrant gravy</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
